The fourth counting number; it is
the second square number, as it is equal to \ensuremath{2 \times 2} or $2^{2}$  (interestingly, it
is also equal to 2+2).
\par
It is also the first tetrahedral number, and the first composite number.
\par
4 is the smallest number which is the square of a prime
number.
\par
It is the number of faces or vertices of a tetrahedron,
the simplest polyhedron.
\par
It is the only composite number n which does not divide
(n-1)!
\par
$ \phi(4)=2, \quad d(4)=3, \quad \sigma(4)=7 . $
